### Suggested Structure
1. **Pages Folder**: Use the `pages` directory for general pages (e.g., Home, About, etc.) and dynamic routes for documentation topics.
2. **Docs Folder**: Create a dedicated folder for MDX files that represent individual documentation topics or pages.
3. **Components Folder**: Add reusable components like a sidebar, navigation bar, and MDX layout wrapper.
4. **Tailwind CSS**: Set up theming for your documents, like colors and typography.

### Steps to Implement
Here’s how to get started:

#### 1. Install Dependencies
Make sure you have MDX enabled:
```bash
npm install @mdx-js/react next-mdx-remote
npm install --save-dev tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init
```

#### 2. Add MDX Support
Use the `next-mdx-remote` library to load MDX content on your pages. Here’s an example dynamic route for your documentation pages:
```tsx
// pages/docs/[slug].tsx
import { getFiles, getFileBySlug } from '../../lib/mdx';
import { MDXRemote } from 'next-mdx-remote';
import { GetStaticPaths, GetStaticProps } from 'next';
import { MDXRemoteSerializeResult } from 'next-mdx-remote';

interface DocPageProps {
  source: MDXRemoteSerializeResult;
  frontMatter: { title: string; description: string };
}

const DocPage = ({ source, frontMatter }: DocPageProps) => (
  <div className="prose mx-auto">
    <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold">{frontMatter.title}</h1>
    <p className="text-gray-600">{frontMatter.description}</p>
    <MDXRemote {...source} />
  </div>
);

export const getStaticPaths: GetStaticPaths = async () => {
  const files = await getFiles('docs');
  const paths = files.map((file) => ({
    params: { slug: file.replace(/\.mdx$/, '') },
  }));

  return { paths, fallback: false };
};

export const getStaticProps: GetStaticProps = async ({ params }) => {
  const { slug } = params!;
  const { source, frontMatter } = await getFileBySlug('docs', slug as string);

  return {
    props: { source, frontMatter },
  };
};

export default DocPage;
```

#### 3. Fetch MDX Files
Create utility functions for reading MDX files:
```ts
// lib/mdx.ts
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';
import matter from 'gray-matter';
import { serialize } from 'next-mdx-remote/serialize';

const ROOT_PATH = process.cwd();
const DOCS_PATH = path.join(ROOT_PATH, 'docs');

export const getFiles = async (folder: string): Promise<string[]> => {
  return fs.readdirSync(path.join(ROOT_PATH, folder));
};

export const getFileBySlug = async (folder: string, slug: string) => {
  const filePath = path.join(ROOT_PATH, folder, `${slug}.mdx`);
  const fileContent = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8');
  const { content, data } = matter(fileContent);
  const mdxSource = await serialize(content);

  return {
    source: mdxSource,
    frontMatter: data,
  };
};
```

#### 4. Style with Tailwind CSS
Update your `tailwind.config.js` to include custom styles:
```js
module.exports = {
  content: ['./pages/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}', './components/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}'],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      typography: {
        DEFAULT: {
          css: {
            color: '#4A5568',
            a: {
              color: '#3182CE',
              '&:hover': {
                color: '#2B6CB0',
              },
            },
          },
        },
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [require('@tailwindcss/typography')],
};
```

#### 5. Create a Sidebar
Add a navigation sidebar to your documentation site:
```tsx
// components/Sidebar.tsx
import Link from 'next/link';

const links = [
  { href: '/docs/getting-started', label: 'Getting Started' },
  { href: '/docs/installation', label: 'Installation' },
];

const Sidebar = () => (
  <aside className="w-64 h-screen bg-gray-100 p-4">
    <nav>
      <ul>
        {links.map((link) => (
          <li key={link.href}>
            <Link href={link.href}>
              <a className="block py-2 px-4 text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-200 hover:text-gray-900">
                {link.label}
              </a>
            </Link>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </aside>
);

export default Sidebar;
```

#### 6. Layout Component
Wrap your MDX content pages in a layout:
```tsx
// components/Layout.tsx
import Sidebar from './Sidebar';

const Layout = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => (
  <div className="flex">
    <Sidebar />
    <main className="flex-1 p-8 bg-white">{children}</main>
  </div>
);

export default Layout;
```

Finally, apply the layout in your dynamic route:
```tsx
import Layout from '../../components/Layout';

const DocPage = ({ source, frontMatter }: DocPageProps) => (
  <Layout>
    <div className="prose mx-auto">
      <h1>{frontMatter.title}</h1>
      <MDXRemote {...source} />
    </div>
  </Layout>
);
```

